msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:5
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:6
msgid "Clone our Quickstart repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:12
msgid ""
"Start your daemon (see [](/quickstart.md) if necessary) and export your "
"client key to environment (see [](/quickstart.md#setup-client-key))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:14
msgid ""
"This Bot embeds an HTTP server to handle webhook entry points. To set it "
"up, you'll need to define the following environment variables:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:17
msgid ""
"WEBHOOK_SERVER_PORT: The port on which the Bot's HTTP server should "
"listen. WEBOOK_SERVER_HOST: The IP address to listen on. "
"WEBHOOK_PUBLIC_URL: The complete URL that allows access to the Bot's "
"server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:21
msgid "Here is an example configuration to use in development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:29
msgid ""
"By using `localhost` as your public url you will only be able to trigger "
"webhook URL from your computer / server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:31
msgid ""
"To trigger from anywhere in the world you will need to setup a reverse "
"proxy exposed on the world (see [](#deploy))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:34
msgid "Run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:35
msgid "Start bot with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:41
msgid "How to use it ?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:42
msgid ""
"When a new conversation is created (i.e., when a new contact is added or "
"the Bot is added to a group), this Bot automatically sets up a webhook "
"entry point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:44
msgid ""
"This allows you to use this entry point to post messages and attachments "
"directly into that specific conversation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:46
msgid ""
"When you started your bot you can use help command to retrieve the "
"webhook URL associated with a discussion.  Simply post `!help` in this "
"discussion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:49
msgid ""
"Then you can use `curl` (or any other way) to make POST requests to this "
"URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../bots/webhook.md:51
msgid ""
"Here are a few example payloads as curl commands (replace WH_URL with the"
" webhook URL provided by your bot)."
msgstr ""

